This paper deals with analyzing topics and intent behind tweets, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses topic modeling techniques, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper deals with finding similar topics between user tweets and BBC news articles. The paper also deals with popularity and attention, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
